I apply topic model to various gene expression datasets, and show the distribution of p values.

Datasets:¶

They are all stored at "/project/mstephens/zihao/count_dataset/".

- GTEx¶

  • processed by Peter Carbonetto. See his process in "/project2/mstephens/pcarbo/git/topics/docs/prepare_gtex.html".
  • It is first downloaded as "GTEx_Analysis_2016-01-15_v7_RNASeQCv1.1.8_gene_reads.gct.gz"
  • I further divide the big data into 30 subtypes by tissue names. Below I will show the result for "brain"

- 10xgenomics¶

  • processed by Abhishek Sarkar.

  • data is from https://www.nature.com/articles/ncomms14049

  • I will show the result for "fresh_68k_pbmc_donor_a"

Experiment setup¶

  • generate training and validation dataset by $X_{\text{train}} \sim Binomial(X, 0.5)$ \begin{align} X_{\text{train}} & \sim Binomial(X, 0.5)\\ X_{\text{valid}} & = X - X_{\text{train}} \end{align}

  • I fit the models described below, then computed the pvalue

Model¶

- General Model¶

\begin{align} X_{ij} & \sim Pois(\Lambda_{ij})\\ \Lambda & \sim f(\phi(\sum_k l_{ik} f_{jk})) \end{align} where $\phi$ is a deterministic function, and $f$ is a distribution.

- NMF¶

I start off with NMF, which has $\Lambda = \sum_k l_{ik} f_{jk}$

- P values¶

p-value (method: NMF_KL)¶

p-value (method: NMF_l2 on log transformed data)¶

\begin{align} Y &= log(X + 1)\\ L,F &<- NMFl2(Y,K)\\ pval &<- pvalue(X, exp(LF' - 1)) \end{align}
